The paper deals with the energy consumption of a decoding algorithm for compressive sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and electronic engineering (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the implementation of the algorithm on a circuit, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents insights into the design of energy-efficient circuits, which is a topic related to electromagnetics (cs.EM).
